  "script": [
    {
      "start": 0.0,
      "end": 13.79,
      "text": "Screen English"
    },
    {
      "start": 13.79,
      "end": 35.05,
      "text": "GMP 영화 구독 서비스, Screen English Time"
    },
    {
      "start": 35.05,
      "end": 37.35,
      "text": "11월에 함께하고 있는 영화는"
    },
    {
      "start": 37.35,
      "end": 38.93,
      "text": "The Seagull, 갈매기"
    },
    {
      "start": 38.93,
      "end": 44.25,
      "text": "It is based on the 1896 play of the same name by Anton Chekhov."
    },
    {
      "start": 44.37,
      "end": 45.51,
      "text": "Wow, good morning."
    },
    {
      "start": 45.77,
      "end": 47.01,
      "text": "Welcome, welcome to Sam."
    },
    {
      "start": 47.01,
      "end": 49.05,
      "text": "Hello, glad to be here as always."
    },
    {
      "start": 49.21,
      "end": 49.55,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 49.55,
      "end": 53.77,
      "text": "이 작품이요, 정말 전 세계적으로"
    },
    {
      "start": 53.77,
      "end": 58.19,
      "text": "특히 연극 무대에서 정말 사랑받는 작품 중에 하나라고"
    },
    {
      "start": 58.19,
      "end": 59.77,
      "text": "이미 말씀을 드렸었는데"
    },
    {
      "start": 59.77,
      "end": 63.89,
      "text": "It was made into a movie in 1968."
    },
    {
      "start": 64.29,
      "end": 65.69,
      "text": "Yeah, way back in 68."
    },
    {
      "start": 65.91,
      "end": 67.71,
      "text": "Wow, it was a long time ago, wasn't it?"
    },
    {
      "start": 67.77,
      "end": 69.91,
      "text": "There have been several movies based on this play."
    },
    {
      "start": 70.37,
      "end": 73.65,
      "text": "This particular movie was directed by Sidney Lumet"
    },
    {
      "start": 73.65,
      "end": 76.11,
      "text": "who's a famous American film director"
    },
    {
      "start": 76.11,
      "end": 81.07,
      "text": "and it was, it got good reviews I think"
    },
    {
      "start": 81.07,
      "end": 83.35,
      "text": "and it was about the same, the same story"
    },
    {
      "start": 83.35,
      "end": 85.19,
      "text": "Yeah, an American movie"
    },
    {
      "start": 85.19,
      "end": 87.61,
      "text": "And this director in particular"
    },
    {
      "start": 87.61,
      "end": 89.63,
      "text": "has made many movies"
    },
    {
      "start": 89.63,
      "end": 92.35,
      "text": "best known for 12 Angry Men"
    },
    {
      "start": 92.35,
      "end": 93.67,
      "text": "back in 1957"
    },
    {
      "start": 93.67,
      "end": 95.61,
      "text": "That was a really famous American movie"
    },
    {
      "start": 95.61,
      "end": 99.07,
      "text": "And then Dog Day Afternoon, 1975"
    },
    {
      "start": 99.07,
      "end": 101.95,
      "text": "about bank robbers who try to rob a bank"
    },
    {
      "start": 101.95,
      "end": 103.83,
      "text": "but everything goes wrong"
    },
    {
      "start": 103.83,
      "end": 106.29,
      "text": "and they can't succeed"
    },
    {
      "start": 106.29,
      "end": 108.71,
      "text": "But the title is Dog Day Afternoon"
    },
    {
      "start": 108.71,
      "end": 109.75,
      "text": "which is very curious"
    },
    {
      "start": 109.75,
      "end": 111.17,
      "text": "Dog Day Afternoon"
    },
    {
      "start": 111.17,
      "end": 113.15,
      "text": "Do you know the dog days?"
    },
    {
      "start": 113.35,
      "end": 114.65,
      "text": "Dog Days라고 하면"
    },
    {
      "start": 114.65,
      "end": 118.11,
      "text": "더운 시즌을 말하는 표현이잖아요"
    },
    {
      "start": 118.11,
      "end": 118.57,
      "text": "Hot"
    },
    {
      "start": 118.57,
      "end": 120.65,
      "text": "Like the 초복, 중복"
    },
    {
      "start": 120.65,
      "end": 121.29,
      "text": "말복"
    },
    {
      "start": 121.29,
      "end": 121.97,
      "text": "말복"
    },
    {
      "start": 121.97,
      "end": 123.95,
      "text": "서양에도 우리나라처럼 이렇게"
    },
    {
      "start": 123.95,
      "end": 125.89,
      "text": "Dog Day라고 부릅니다"
    },
    {
      "start": 125.89,
      "end": 127.23,
      "text": "Dog Days of Summer"
    },
    {
      "start": 127.23,
      "end": 127.79,
      "text": "맞아요"
    },
    {
      "start": 127.79,
      "end": 128.69,
      "text": "Yes"
    },
    {
      "start": 128.69,
      "end": 131.53,
      "text": "이게 특히 별자리 중에서"
    },
    {
      "start": 131.53,
      "end": 133.49,
      "text": "Sirius 별자리 있잖아요"
    },
    {
      "start": 133.49,
      "end": 135.27,
      "text": "Is a very bright star"
    },
    {
      "start": 135.27,
      "end": 138.97,
      "text": "그게 큰 개자리라고도 이야기를 하지 않습니까"
    },
    {
      "start": 138.97,
      "end": 140.89,
      "text": "It's also known as the Dog Star"
    },
    {
      "start": 140.89,
      "end": 144.55,
      "text": "Yeah, 이 별이 태양하고 같이 떠오르게 되면"
    },
    {
      "start": 144.55,
      "end": 146.39,
      "text": "그게 엄청 더운 때가 된대요"
    },
    {
      "start": 146.39,
      "end": 149.07,
      "text": "그래가지고 Dog Days라고 이야기를 하게 됐대요"
    },
    {
      "start": 149.07,
      "end": 151.21,
      "text": "Yeah, so it has nothing to do with dogs"
    },
    {
      "start": 151.21,
      "end": 153.07,
      "text": "Nothing to do with mongmongies"
    },
    {
      "start": 153.07,
      "end": 156.59,
      "text": "전혀 mongmongie하고 상관이 없는 명칭이 되겠습니다"
    },
    {
      "start": 156.59,
      "end": 158.29,
      "text": "It goes way back to astrology"
    },
    {
      "start": 158.29,
      "end": 160.51,
      "text": "From the ancient Roman and Greek times"
    },
    {
      "start": 160.51,
      "end": 163.55,
      "text": "Yeah, that star series was called the dog star"
    },
    {
      "start": 163.55,
      "end": 166.27,
      "text": "And so late July, early August"
    },
    {
      "start": 166.27,
      "end": 168.89,
      "text": "Those are called the Dog Days of Summer"
    },
    {
      "start": 168.89,
      "end": 171.39,
      "text": "이런 상식까지 또 알아가게 되네요"
    },
    {
      "start": 171.39,
      "end": 172.95,
      "text": "Yeah, we don't have Cho Jung My Book"
    },
    {
      "start": 172.95,
      "end": 174.61,
      "text": "We just have the Dog Days"
    },
    {
      "start": 174.61,
      "end": 178.49,
      "text": "Yeah, 아무튼 이 미국의 영화감독인"
    },
    {
      "start": 178.49,
      "end": 181.19,
      "text": "Sidney Lumet라는 이름의 감독이"
    },
    {
      "start": 181.19,
      "end": 185.33,
      "text": "이미도 이 영화화한 사람이라는 것을"
    },
    {
      "start": 185.33,
      "end": 186.55,
      "text": "우리가 알게 되었습니다"
    },
    {
      "start": 186.55,
      "end": 188.53,
      "text": "그리고 아주 유명한 분이죠"
    },
    {
      "start": 188.53,
      "end": 192.01,
      "text": "아카데미상 후보에도 다섯 번이나 오르셨대요"
    },
    {
      "start": 192.01,
      "end": 192.83,
      "text": "Five times!"
    },
    {
      "start": 192.93,
      "end": 193.15,
      "text": "Yeah!"
    },
    {
      "start": 193.27,
      "end": 196.15,
      "text": "Nominated for an Academy Award for Best Director"
    },
    {
      "start": 196.15,
      "end": 196.59,
      "text": "Wow!"
    },
    {
      "start": 197.51,
      "end": 200.27,
      "text": "자, 아무튼 오늘 장면 먼저 듣고 오겠습니다"
    },
    {
      "start": 200.27,
      "end": 205.55,
      "text": "Some people can barely crawl through their dull, obscure existence"
    },
    {
      "start": 205.55,
      "end": 211.01,
      "text": "But you get a life that's brilliant, interesting, meaningful"
    },
    {
      "start": 211.01,
      "end": 212.09,
      "text": "You're happy"
    },
    {
      "start": 212.09,
      "end": 213.87,
      "text": "Am I?"
    },
    {
      "start": 215.28,
      "end": 217.42,
      "text": "Here you are talking about fame, happiness"
    },
    {
      "start": 217.42,
      "end": 219.18,
      "text": "To me, you sound a bit naive"
    },
    {
      "start": 219.18,
      "end": 221.94,
      "text": "Well, to me, you sound jaded and pompous"
    },
    {
      "start": 221.94,
      "end": 226.61,
      "text": "Oh, I thought Nina was like a morality"
    },
    {
      "start": 226.61,
      "end": 229.23,
      "text": "She's a moral girl?"
    },
    {
      "start": 229.23,
      "end": 232.09,
      "text": "네, 아니요, morality가 lack of"
    },
    {
      "start": 232.09,
      "end": 233.81,
      "text": "부족한 것 같아요"
    },
    {
      "start": 233.81,
      "end": 234.37,
      "text": "Ah, immoral"
    },
    {
      "start": 234.37,
      "end": 234.69,
      "text": "Yeah"
    },
    {
      "start": 234.69,
      "end": 235.65,
      "text": "도덕성 없는"
    },
    {
      "start": 235.65,
      "end": 236.29,
      "text": "Yeah"
    },
    {
      "start": 236.29,
      "end": 237.41,
      "text": "도덕성 어딘야?"
    },
    {
      "start": 237.49,
      "end": 240.39,
      "text": "왜냐하면 이 남자친구인 컨스탄틴"
    },
    {
      "start": 240.39,
      "end": 242.41,
      "text": "아직 완전히 헤어진 상태도 아니잖아요"
    },
    {
      "start": 242.41,
      "end": 244.71,
      "text": "Oh, that was her official boyfriend, right?"
    },
    {
      "start": 244.71,
      "end": 244.89,
      "text": "Yeah"
    },
    {
      "start": 244.89,
      "end": 247.53,
      "text": "In the beginning of the movie, they were hugging and kissing"
    },
    {
      "start": 247.53,
      "end": 248.13,
      "text": "She was saying"
    },
    {
      "start": 248.13,
      "end": 249.31,
      "text": "Oh my gosh"
    },
    {
      "start": 249.31,
      "end": 258.93,
      "text": "Oh, 그리고 또 컨스탄틴의 엄마인 이리나의 애인인 보리스한테 지금 유혹을 살짝쿵 하고 있는 그런 장면이기 때문에"
    },
    {
      "start": 258.93,
      "end": 262.45,
      "text": "With lack of morality 이렇게 생각을 하게 된 겁니다"
    },
    {
      "start": 262.45,
      "end": 264.85,
      "text": "Yeah, I would say she's cheating on her boyfriend"
    },
    {
      "start": 264.85,
      "end": 267.05,
      "text": "She hasn't officially broken up"
    },
    {
      "start": 267.05,
      "end": 268.37,
      "text": "I don't think so"
    },
    {
      "start": 268.37,
      "end": 272.19,
      "text": "And now she's flirting with this new guy, 보리스"
    },
    {
      "start": 272.19,
      "end": 275.53,
      "text": "이렇게 유혹을 슬슬 시작을 하고 있습니다"
    },
    {
      "start": 275.53,
      "end": 279.19,
      "text": "주요 표현들 먼저 살펴볼까요?"
    },
    {
      "start": 279.43,
      "end": 280.87,
      "text": "Barely crawl through"
    },
    {
      "start": 280.87,
      "end": 285.29,
      "text": "Barely 라고 하면 거의 뭐뭐하지 못하다 라고 해석을 하셔야 됩니다"
    },
    {
      "start": 285.29,
      "end": 286.13,
      "text": "Barely"
    },
    {
      "start": 286.13,
      "end": 289.57,
      "text": "그 다음 crawl through 라고 들렸잖아요"
    },
    {
      "start": 289.57,
      "end": 292.61,
      "text": "C-R-A-W-L"
    },
    {
      "start": 292.61,
      "end": 295.33,
      "text": "기다 라는 동사이기도 한데"
    },
    {
      "start": 295.33,
      "end": 299.19,
      "text": "Crawl through 그리고 barely 와 함께 들려가지고"
    },
    {
      "start": 299.19,
      "end": 302.71,
      "text": "거의 통과하지 못하다 라고 해석이 됩니다"
    },
    {
      "start": 302.71,
      "end": 305.09,
      "text": "Yeah, like when I eat a lot"
    },
    {
      "start": 305.09,
      "end": 307.63,
      "text": "and then I try to get out of my car"
    },
    {
      "start": 307.63,
      "end": 309.19,
      "text": "when it's close to another car"
    },
    {
      "start": 309.19,
      "end": 311.89,
      "text": "and I just can barely make it out"
    },
    {
      "start": 311.89,
      "end": 314.33,
      "text": "So it's good to have a lot of space"
    },
    {
      "start": 314.33,
      "end": 315.97,
      "text": "when you're getting out of your car"
    },
    {
      "start": 315.97,
      "end": 317.19,
      "text": "after you park"
    },
    {
      "start": 317.19,
      "end": 317.59,
      "text": "Yeah"
    },
    {
      "start": 317.59,
      "end": 318.71,
      "text": "You ever have those days?"
    },
    {
      "start": 318.85,
      "end": 321.11,
      "text": "Oh, you're very slender, so"
    },
    {
      "start": 321.11,
      "end": 321.47,
      "text": "Yeah"
    },
    {
      "start": 321.47,
      "end": 322.15,
      "text": "Maybe not"
    },
    {
      "start": 322.15,
      "end": 322.75,
      "text": "Oh, 그래요?"
    },
    {
      "start": 322.93,
      "end": 324.95,
      "text": "엄청 먹고 나서 차 내릴 때 있잖아요"
    },
    {
      "start": 324.95,
      "end": 327.61,
      "text": "그 옆에 차 좀 차이가 없을 때"
    },
    {
      "start": 327.61,
      "end": 330.59,
      "text": "Barely, I can barely make it out of my car"
    },
    {
      "start": 330.59,
      "end": 332.93,
      "text": "네, 종종 경험을 한 것 같기도 하고"
    },
    {
      "start": 332.93,
      "end": 334.63,
      "text": "말하기도 좀 그렇기도 하고"
    },
    {
      "start": 334.63,
      "end": 336.31,
      "text": "That's just me, my personal experience"
    },
    {
      "start": 336.31,
      "end": 337.15,
      "text": "Not you"
    },
    {
      "start": 337.15,
      "end": 338.73,
      "text": "다음 표현도 들어볼까요?"
    },
    {
      "start": 339.23,
      "end": 340.53,
      "text": "Sound a bit naive"
    },
    {
      "start": 340.53,
      "end": 342.85,
      "text": "네, sound a bit naive"
    },
    {
      "start": 342.85,
      "end": 343.67,
      "text": "Naive"
    },
    {
      "start": 343.67,
      "end": 344.89,
      "text": "Yeah, naive"
    },
    {
      "start": 344.89,
      "end": 348.33,
      "text": "N-A-I-V-E"
    },
    {
      "start": 348.33,
      "end": 349.31,
      "text": "라는 철자입니다"
    },
    {
      "start": 349.31,
      "end": 351.73,
      "text": "다소 naive"
    },
    {
      "start": 351.73,
      "end": 353.05,
      "text": "하게 들리다"
    },
    {
      "start": 353.05,
      "end": 355.01,
      "text": "순진하게 들리다"
    },
    {
      "start": 355.01,
      "end": 356.01,
      "text": "라는 표현이에요"
    },
    {
      "start": 356.01,
      "end": 356.89,
      "text": "Yeah, naive"
    },
    {
      "start": 356.89,
      "end": 358.01,
      "text": "It's like innocent"
    },
    {
      "start": 358.01,
      "end": 359.95,
      "text": "but not in a good way"
    },
    {
      "start": 359.95,
      "end": 362.07,
      "text": "It's too innocent"
    },
    {
      "start": 362.07,
      "end": 363.13,
      "text": "in a bad way"
    },
    {
      "start": 363.13,
      "end": 364.45,
      "text": "Yeah, 순수가 아닌"
    },
    {
      "start": 364.45,
      "end": 365.53,
      "text": "순진"
    },
    {
      "start": 365.53,
      "end": 367.99,
      "text": "약간 좀 부정적인 의미가 느껴지죠"
    },
    {
      "start": 367.99,
      "end": 369.05,
      "text": "Yeah, 순진"
    },
    {
      "start": 369.05,
      "end": 371.67,
      "text": "순수보다는 좀 부정적인"
    },
    {
      "start": 371.67,
      "end": 372.17,
      "text": "그 정도?"
    },
    {
      "start": 372.45,
      "end": 372.67,
      "text": "Yeah"
    },
    {
      "start": 372.67,
      "end": 373.17,
      "text": "Yeah"
    },
    {
      "start": 373.17,
      "end": 374.17,
      "text": "세상 잘 모르는"
    },
    {
      "start": 374.17,
      "end": 375.29,
      "text": "세상을 잘 모르는"
    },
    {
      "start": 375.29,
      "end": 376.71,
      "text": "아, 세상 물정 잘 모르는"
    },
    {
      "start": 376.71,
      "end": 377.17,
      "text": "Yeah, 그거"
    },
    {
      "start": 377.17,
      "end": 380.75,
      "text": "Jaded and pompous"
    },
    {
      "start": 380.75,
      "end": 381.63,
      "text": "Jaded"
    },
    {
      "start": 381.63,
      "end": 382.75,
      "text": "철자 알려드릴게요"
    },
    {
      "start": 382.75,
